          }, this), /*#__PURE__*/_jsxDEV("p", {
            children: "What makes Net art so powerful is that the Internet user is not merely a viewer or guest but is actively involved in, and contributes to the net art experience - a unique situation, not often present in other media, and one that decentralises and breaks down hierarchies of authorship (Greene 2004) [4]. Net art challenges preconceived notions of what the web is, how it works and how users participate and experience life online. 4 key factors that designers must take into consideration when designing for the online environment are: Invisible design elements, collaborative participation, anarchic structure and non-linear communication."
          }, void 0, false, {
